{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow drinks to contain up to 2mg of THC and CBN",
        "additional_details": "1) Allows customers to go to a pub, and realistically replace alcohol with THC drinks which would have a similar inebriation as alcohol.\r\n2) It could allow safe dosing for customers.\r\n3) It could be strong enough for medical use without overpowering users.\r\n4) It could disincentivise smoking.\r\n5) It could reduce drinking and reduce health risks associated with it.",
        "background": "We propose to amend legislation governing controlled drugs to allow drinks to contain up to 2mg of THC and CBN. We believe it\u2019s the perfect amount and could have a number of benefits: https://littlerick.co.uk/blogs/cannabinoids/cbd-drink-uk",
